n = 2^4 \cdot 3^5 \cdot 2^{12} \cdot 2^7 \cdot 3^7 = 2^{4+12+7} \cdot 3^{5+7} = 2^{23} \cdot 3^{12}
\] The number of factors of a number \( n = p_1^{e_1} \cdot p_2^{e_2} \cdot \ldots \cdot p_k^{e_k} \) is given by \((e_1 + 1)(e_2 + 1) \ldots (e_k + 1)\). Thus, the number of natural-number factors of \( n = 2^{23} \cdot 3^{12} \) is \((23 + 1)(12 + 1) = 24 \cdot 13 = 312\). </think> <answer> 312 </answer>
